{
  "stem": "14002.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In that camp itself, they had like small factories.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They had, let's say, tailor shops, where they made outfits for the soldiers, for the German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They had a shoemaker's shop where they made shoes for the soldiers, and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When we came down from the train, one guy what was already in that camp, a Yiddish fellow, says to me-- he said like this here, [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In other words, say that you have a trade.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "As I knew a little bit of shoemakers, I said, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I'm a shoemaker.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My brother, he was young.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They put him as a-- what to clean-- what to clean the barrack where we were living.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Me, they assigned as a shoemaker in a shoe factory to make shoes for the German-- for the German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The food-- The food consisted there of barley soup and a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There was on the other side== there were men and women, but they were separated with barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Almost every day, every day I used to see somebody committing suicide.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He threw himself on the-- on the electric wires, on the electric current.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Almost every day, somebody did it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The-- the guards, the German guards-- special the women that I have seen-- were much more brutal than the men guards in Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "One day, I've seen, they caught about three Jews in Krakow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] They lined them up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They made them dig a trench.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They lined them up against the trench over there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was-- I'll never forget that picture of that person.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "One guy had red hair.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "When they put the machine gun in the front of them, and we-- they told-- and we had to watch that.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
